# {{PROJECT}}-app

Mobile app for {{PROJECT}}. {{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}

Flutter + Riverpod (code-gen) + go_router + Dio.

## First-time setup

```bash
flutter pub get
cp .env.example .env
dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
flutter run
```

The `build_runner` step is **required** on every fresh clone вЂ” `*.g.dart`,
`*.freezed.dart`, `*.mocks.dart`, and `*.config.dart` are gitignored. The app
will not compile until they're generated.

The Android emulator resolves `localhost` on the host as `10.0.2.2` вЂ” that's
why `.env.example` points the API base at `http://10.0.2.2:3030`. iOS simulator
uses `localhost` directly. Edit `.env` for a physical device (LAN IP).

After every change to `.env` or any `@riverpod`/`@Envied`-annotated file,
re-run the build runner.

