## Conventions

- Riverpod with `@riverpod` annotations only вЂ” never raw `Provider(...)` / `StateNotifier(...)` for new code
- `go_router` for navigation вЂ” never `Navigator.push` directly
- API calls go through `lib/core/network/api_client.dart` вЂ” never construct Dio in feature code
- Auth tokens via `AuthStorage` (FlutterSecureStorage) вЂ” never SharedPreferences for secrets
- Every request carries `{{API_VERSION_HEADER}}: {{API_VERSION_DEFAULT}}` (set by the Dio base options вЂ” no per-call work)
- Errors caught from the API are `ApiError` instances вЂ” switch on `code` (string from `ErrorCodes`), never on HTTP status

## Hard rules

- Never call `Navigator.push` вЂ” use `context.go(...)` / `context.push(...)` / `context.goNamed(...)`
- Never hardcode an API URL or secret вЂ” env config only
- Never bypass the auth interceptor вЂ” every authed request must carry the bearer token (or be on a route gated to signed-out)
- Never target widgets by visible text in E2E specs вЂ” Keys only
- Never put business logic in a Widget вЂ” it lives in `@riverpod` notifiers
